&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an AI Architect you will define scalable and resilient AI agent architectures while establishing reusable patterns, components, and frameworks to support consistent and efficient development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement scalable, fault-tolerant agentic architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain traceability, monitoring, and evaluation mechanisms for AI systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement guardrails and security measures to ensure safe and compliant AI usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and optimize Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines and vector search frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with stakeholders to define requirements and communicate technical concepts effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate the feasibility, practicality, and risks associated with AI architectures and workflows.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of agentic architectural patterns and their practical applications in technology and finance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in agentic orchestration frameworks (e.g., LangGraph or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on expertise in Python, with knowledge of both API-first development practices and traditional service-based architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with traceability, monitoring, and evaluation techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of cloud platforms and experience designing cloud-based AI solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of AI governance principles and practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills for collaboration across technical and non-technical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in German and English&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver high-impact, &lt;strong&gt;transformational data strategies&lt;/strong&gt; for leading financial institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a &lt;strong&gt;collaborative, entrepreneurial culture&lt;/strong&gt; where your ideas shape the future.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access &lt;strong&gt;continuous learning&lt;/strong&gt;, training, and industry certifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence not only client outcomes but also the &lt;strong&gt;strategic direction&lt;/strong&gt; of our data practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of a team that’s redefining the &lt;strong&gt;future of digital financial services&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capco’s &lt;strong&gt;#BeYourselfAtWork culture&lt;/strong&gt; means we celebrate individuality and work in an environment where diverse perspectives truly drive results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re ready to &lt;strong&gt;lead transformation, challenge the status quo, and leave a lasting impact&lt;/strong&gt; on the financial services data landscape, we’d like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-start=&quot;5779&quot; data-end=&quot;6234&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;AI Business Analyst&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: London (Hybrid) | Practice Area: Capital Markets | Type: Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help leading Capital Markets organisations turn AI opportunities into scalable business solutions across front, middle, and back-office operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join Capco’s Capital Markets practice as an AI Business Analyst, helping investment banks, exchanges, market infrastructure providers, broker-dealers, asset managers, and trading organisations bridge the gap between emerging AI capabilities and practical business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of business analysis, AI enablement, and transformation delivery, supporting clients as they identify, prioritise, and implement AI-driven solutions across trading, operations, risk, compliance, regulatory reporting, client servicing, and post-trade functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with business stakeholders, product owners, delivery teams, and AI specialists to define use cases, analyse processes, gather requirements, and support the successful delivery of AI-enabled solutions within complex and highly regulated Capital Markets environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside transformation delivery, you will help clients navigate AI adoption responsibly, balancing innovation with governance, operational risk, model oversight, and regulatory expectations. You will contribute to process optimisation, AI performance measurement, business readiness, and change adoption activities, ensuring AI solutions deliver measurable business value while supporting operational resilience and regulatory compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work with Capital Markets stakeholders across Front Office, Middle Office, Operations, Risk, Compliance, and Technology teams to identify, analyse, and define AI-enabled opportunities, including Generative AI and agentic workflow use cases that improve productivity, decision-making, and operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Facilitate workshops, gather and document requirements, map business processes, and support the translation of trading, post-trade, regulatory, and operational challenges into practical AI-enabled solutions with measurable business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support Agile and hybrid delivery programmes by contributing to backlog refinement, user stories, acceptance criteria, stakeholder coordination, reporting, and governance activities using approved AI tools where they enhance speed, quality, or insight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner with AI engineers, architects, product owners, and business SMEs to support the development, testing, validation, and deployment of AI-enabled capabilities across Capital Markets functions while ensuring outputs remain aligned to business requirements and regulatory obligations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support responsible AI adoption by contributing to governance, operational risk management, regulatory compliance, change management, training, and business readiness activities, including human-in-the-loop controls, auditability, escalation pathways, and monitoring frameworks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working as a Business Analyst, Consultant, or transformation professional within Capital Markets environments, with strong exposure to Investment Banking, Equities, Fixed Income, FX, Commodities, Derivatives, Prime Services, Securities Services, or Market Infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong stakeholder management, requirements gathering, workshop facilitation, and communication skills, with the ability to translate technical AI

