&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Transformation Managing Principal – Banking&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; New York, NY | &lt;strong&gt;Practice Area:&lt;/strong&gt; Technology &amp;amp; Engineering | &lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead AI transformation strategies that redefine banking.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an AI Transformation Managing Principal – Banking, you will partner with leading banking institutions to drive enterprise AI transformation initiatives that modernize operations, enhance customer experiences, and accelerate innovation. You will define AI strategy, identify high-value business opportunities, and oversee delivery alongside cross-functional teams. This senior consulting role combines AI strategy, business transformation, banking expertise, and executive client engagement to deliver scalable, business-focused AI solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead enterprise AI and Generative AI transformation programs for banking clients, aligning AI investments with business strategy and measurable outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define AI roadmaps, operating models, and transformation strategies spanning foundation models, agentic AI, intelligent automation, and emerging AI capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise executive stakeholders across retail, commercial, corporate, and digital banking on AI opportunities in lending, customer servicing, operations, risk, compliance, and back-office transformation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with architecture, engineering, data, and delivery teams to develop, pilot, and scale enterprise AI solutions while building trusted executive client relationships and identifying new consulting opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor consulting teams, strengthen AI capabilities within the Banking practice, and contribute to thought leadership, market offerings, and industry initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of consulting and technology transformation experience, including enterprise AI, AI/ML, or Generative AI strategy, with a proven track record delivering transformation within the banking sector.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of banking operations, digital banking, lending, customer experience, risk, compliance, and enterprise transformation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success building executive client relationships, leading complex consulting engagements, and supporting business development initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of foundation models, agentic AI, enterprise AI platforms, and the ability to translate emerging technologies into measurable business value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and executive presentation skills, with the ability to bridge business strategy and technical delivery. Willingness to work from our New York office three days per week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing enterprise AI strategies for retail, commercial, corporate, or digital banking organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing AI operating models, governance frameworks, and enterprise adoption strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Responsible AI practices, including governance, explainability, fairness, risk management, and regulatory considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience applying AI to lending, customer servicing, fraud prevention, financial crime, banking operations, or regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributions to thought leadership, client workshops, industry events, or AI-focused market offerings within the banking industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
